article.linkText: Duquesne beats Ball State 78-77, Clark beats buzzer twice
article.story: PITTSBURGH -- — Jimmy Clark III hit a 3-pointer at the buzzer and scored 16 points to give Duquesne a 78-77 win over Ball State 78-77. Clark, who also hit a 3 at the halftime buzzer, had six rebounds for the Dukes (7-1). Tevin Brewer scored 14 points while shooting 5 for 10, including 4 for 5 from beyond the arc. Dae Dae Grant recorded 11 points and shot 3 for 10 (2 for 5 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free throw line. The Dukes prolonged their winning streak to six games. The Cardinals (4-4) were led by Jaylin Sellers, who posted 22 points. Ball State also got 12 points from Demarius Jacobs. Jarron Coleman also had 11 points and five assists. Clark scored 11 points in the first half and Duquesne went into the break trailing 40-36. Duquesne outscored Ball State by five points in the second half. David Dixon led the way with seven second-half points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
